# UI & Tailwind Rules

## General UI Principles

- Default to clean, minimal UI with clear hierarchy.
- Aim for one primary action per view when possible; de-emphasize secondary actions.
- Prioritize legibility:
  - Adequate spacing (padding/margin),
  - Clear type scale (e.g., `text-xs`, `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`).

## Tailwind Usage

- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling in React/Next components.
- Avoid large custom CSS files unless there is a clear shared pattern.
- Prefer composing Tailwind utilities directly over heavy use of `@apply`.

## ClassName Organization

- Keep `className` values readable by roughly grouping utilities:
  - Layout (e.g., `flex`, `grid`, `gap-*`),
  - Spacing (e.g., `p-*`, `m-*`),
  - Typography (e.g., `text-*`, `font-*`),
  - Color/border (e.g., `bg-*`, `text-*`, `border-*`, `shadow-*`).

## Design Tokens & Colors

- Prefer project-defined color tokens (Tailwind config, CSS variables) over ad-hoc hex values.
- Maintain consistent background/text/accent colors to match the brand.
- Avoid introducing brand-new colors without aligning them with the existing palette.

## Layout & Responsiveness

- Use Tailwind's responsive utilities (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`) rather than manual media queries when possible.
- Common pattern:
  - Mobile: stacked layouts (`flex-col`, `grid-cols-1`),
  - Desktop: split layouts (`md:grid-cols-2`, `lg:grid-cols-3`, etc.).
- Ensure primary actions are easily tappable on mobile (sufficient height and spacing).

## Components & Reuse

- When a UI pattern appears in multiple places (cards, buttons, form layouts), consider extracting a reusable component.
- Keep components focused; avoid god components that handle unrelated responsibilities.
- Use existing components as reference for styling and behavior to maintain visual consistency.

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements where possible (`button`, `nav`, `header`, `main`, etc.).
- Ensure interactive elements have visible focus states (Tailwind `ring` utilities, `focus:outline-none focus:ring-2`).
- Provide appropriate ARIA labels when semantic HTML is insufficient.
- Maintain sufficient color contrast ratios for text and interactive elements.
- Ensure keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements.
